1
00:00:00,462 --> 00:00:01,851
Previously on Jericho

2
00:00:02,199 --> 00:00:03,414
<i>Bring them inside.</i>

3
00:00:03,568 --> 00:00:04,899
<i>Some of them were on planes</i>

4
00:00:04,900 --> 00:00:06,809
<i>that landed in
the middle of nowhere.</i>

5
00:00:07,022 --> 00:00:08,623
<i>They've been walking
for weeks.</i>

6
00:00:08,932 --> 00:00:10,639
<i>They must have gone
through hell.</i>

7
00:00:10,640 --> 00:00:13,631
<i>Oh, my God... Roger.</i>

8
00:00:14,299 --> 00:00:16,710
<i>You have moderate frostbite
on your toes and fingers.</i>

9
00:00:16,711 --> 00:00:18,370
<i>You need to keep
them clean and warm.</i>

10
00:00:18,446 --> 00:00:19,990
<i>Do you know anyone
in Jericho?</i>

11
00:00:20,164 --> 00:00:22,402
<i>Actually... I do.</i>

12
00:00:24,072 --> 00:00:25,171
<i>Hello, Rob.</i>

13
00:00:25,442 --> 00:00:27,699
<i>We're using the generator
to power the town hall</i>

14
00:00:27,700 --> 00:00:30,043
<i>for three hours a day,
the Med Center for six.</i>

15
00:00:30,244 --> 00:00:33,602
<i>With 53 new people, at current
levels of consumption...</i>

16
00:00:34,023 --> 00:00:37,399
<i>we will be completely out
of gas and diesel in two weeks.</i>

17
00:00:37,591 --> 00:00:40,118
<i>- Mrs. Green?
- What?</i>

18
00:00:40,331 --> 00:00:42,134
<i>Eric told me that
April's pregnant.</i>

19
00:00:42,453 --> 00:00:43,822
<i>It's the Old Man.</i>

20
00:00:44,070 --> 00:00:46,424
<i>He's coming for us
using us against each other.</i>

21
00:00:46,482 --> 00:00:49,627
<i>We go see him and if,
if he is behind this,</i>

22
00:00:49,839 --> 00:00:50,842
<i>We take him out.</i>

23
00:00:50,900 --> 00:00:52,733
<i>We leave first thing
in the morning.</i>

24
00:01:18,299 --> 00:01:19,823
<i>Any luck out there?</i>

25
00:01:19,997 --> 00:01:21,251
Sorry, ma'am.

26
00:01:24,415 --> 00:01:26,614
Nothing?
Not even rabbits?

27
00:01:27,154 --> 00:01:28,773
Never seen anything
like it before.

28
00:01:28,774 --> 00:01:30,202
Nothing moving out there.

29
00:01:30,369 --> 00:01:33,629
Think it was the fallout? Maybe it was
the radiation that killed the deer.

30
00:01:33,677 --> 00:01:35,519
There'd still be dead animals,
carcasses, something.

31
00:01:35,520 --> 00:01:36,364
I mean, it was weird.

32
00:01:36,365 --> 00:01:37,623
Like all the game had vanished.

33
00:01:37,920 --> 00:01:38,923
How far out
did you go?

34
00:01:38,962 --> 00:01:42,628
15 miles out by Mill Pond
along the creek there.

35
00:01:42,748 --> 00:01:44,672
Guess we're going to have
to drive, huh, Jake?

36
00:01:44,673 --> 00:01:47,685
Yeah, but we have to be careful
about burning the gas rations

37
00:01:47,686 --> 00:01:48,688
in the middle of winter.

38
00:01:48,746 --> 00:01:50,674
We need everything we can
to run the generator.

39
00:01:50,675 --> 00:01:52,237
We can live without
power for now.

40
00:01:52,778 --> 00:01:53,965
Make fires to stay warm.

41
00:01:54,341 --> 00:01:56,386
But we won't see Spring
if we don't eat.

42
00:01:56,463 --> 00:01:59,367
Stanley and I will have to use
whatever gas we can spare.

43
00:01:59,607 --> 00:02:01,564
and go out west,
Go out as far as it takes.

44
00:02:01,565 --> 00:02:04,372
The rest of the hunting parties
will have to scrounge around locally.

45
00:02:04,373 --> 00:02:06,392
Yeah, and Mimi's coming
with us.

46
00:02:07,318 --> 00:02:08,118
What?

47
00:02:09,460 --> 00:02:12,363
Well, in case something happens to me,
I want to make sure she knows...

48
00:02:12,382 --> 00:02:13,785
how to trap and shoot, okay?

49
00:02:16,926 --> 00:02:19,550
Look, the further you get
the hairier the roads are.

50
00:02:19,588 --> 00:02:21,074
With food being
as scarce as it is,

51
00:02:21,075 --> 00:02:22,848
there's bound to be
some trouble out there.

52
00:02:22,849 --> 00:02:25,164
That sleeping bag's
rated to 40 below

53
00:02:25,284 --> 00:02:28,327
and here's a wind-proof lighter for you.
You're going to need them both.

54
00:02:28,674 --> 00:02:29,759
Good hunting.

55
00:02:32,653 --> 00:02:34,659
I'm guessing the good folks
of Jericho don't know

56
00:02:34,660 --> 00:02:37,611
about all this stuff down here.
- They don't know about a lot of things.

57
00:02:37,767 --> 00:02:39,884
That'll be enough to get us
to the Old Man's place?

58
00:02:39,885 --> 00:02:41,982
He is only about
two hours away.

59
00:02:42,151 --> 00:02:43,984
I didn't realize
he was so close.

60
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:45,624
He chose the rally point.

61
00:02:46,096 --> 00:02:47,784
Wanted it in his backyard.

62
00:02:47,785 --> 00:02:49,366
How long as he been
watching you?

63
00:02:50,340 --> 00:02:51,729
My guess...

64
00:02:51,730 --> 00:02:54,256
since I stopped communications
a few days ago.

65
00:02:55,589 --> 00:02:57,769
You worried about what we're
going to find out there?

66
00:02:57,770 --> 00:02:59,969
- You're not.
- We can handle him.

67
00:03:00,509 --> 00:03:03,287
It's you and me.
Let's get to work.

68
00:03:07,874 --> 00:03:09,706
My grandmother
went fast than this

69
00:03:09,707 --> 00:03:11,250
and she didn't
even have a car.

70
00:03:11,385 --> 00:03:13,469
We have to take it easy,
we only have half a tank.

71
00:03:13,470 --> 00:03:15,224
Well, hopefully we'll make it
to Flint Springs. It's got...

72
00:03:15,225 --> 00:03:16,652
Hopefully? What do you
mean "hopefully"?

73
00:03:16,653 --> 00:03:18,752
It's got a river.
It's prime white-tailed terrain.

74
00:03:18,771 --> 00:03:19,909
I know, but...
This is crazy.

75
00:03:19,910 --> 00:03:21,877
I told you that
I can't hunt.

76
00:03:21,878 --> 00:03:23,112
Now you want me to kill Bambi.

77
00:03:23,113 --> 00:03:24,386
You're gonna have to
learn, all right?

78
00:03:24,387 --> 00:03:26,392
Everyone's doing their part.
Bonnie's been out twice.

79
00:03:26,393 --> 00:03:27,675
Well, good for
frickin' Bonnie.

80
00:03:27,676 --> 00:03:29,025
Bonnie grew up on farm.

81
00:03:29,026 --> 00:03:30,761
The closest I ever got
to the outdoors

82
00:03:30,762 --> 00:03:32,923
was the is the Ralph Lauren
section of Neiman Marcus.

83
00:03:32,956 --> 00:03:34,099
There you go,
bargain hunting.

84
00:03:34,100 --> 00:03:35,314
Same thing, but with a gun.

85
00:03:35,315 --> 00:03:37,330
Bargains? At Neimans?

86
00:03:37,546 --> 00:03:38,356
Sometimes I forget

87
00:03:38,357 --> 00:03:40,536
that the biggest designer
in your closet is Wrangler.

88
00:03:42,214 --> 00:03:43,304
What are you
laughing at?

89
00:03:43,410 --> 00:03:45,571
I've never seen you in a
domestic squabble before.

90
00:03:45,572 --> 00:03:47,341
Knock it off.
This isn't squabbling.

91
00:03:51,836 --> 00:03:52,801
Oh, my God.

92
00:03:56,097 --> 00:03:57,930
These dogs have tags.

93
00:04:03,271 --> 00:04:04,544
Look at all this.

94
00:04:09,294 --> 00:04:10,528
Wall Drugs.

95
00:04:10,991 --> 00:04:12,342
Wall, South Dakota.

96
00:04:12,418 --> 00:04:14,862
Do you think that's where all
these people were coming from?

97
00:04:14,863 --> 00:04:15,795
Think about it.

98
00:04:16,108 --> 00:04:18,655
South Dakota without heat,
electricity, or...

99
00:04:19,214 --> 00:04:20,526
food being trucked in.

100
00:04:20,545 --> 00:04:22,475
It's got to be even worse
in North Dakota,

101
00:04:22,476 --> 00:04:23,381
Montana.

102
00:04:27,142 --> 00:04:28,338
Oh, my God.

103
00:04:40,726 --> 00:04:43,505
I read about this
at Blackjack.

104
00:04:44,269 --> 00:04:48,050
Mass migration, hundreds...
maybe thousands of people

105
00:04:48,783 --> 00:04:49,941
heading south.

106
00:04:52,121 --> 00:04:53,606
Trying to outrun winter.

107
00:04:54,819 --> 00:04:56,594
Should we be doing
that, too?

108
00:05:09,752 --> 00:05:12,742
Season 1 - Episode 14
" Heart Of Winter "

109
00:05:12,743 --> 00:05:14,744
[ Transcript ]
swsub.com

110
00:05:14,745 --> 00:05:16,750
[ Synchro ]
mOOchie / Loky / aSpro5oo

111
00:05:16,751 --> 00:05:19,740
[ www.seriessub.com ]

112
00:05:21,752 --> 00:05:22,929
How far is it?

113
00:05:24,974 --> 00:05:25,997
...60.

114
00:05:26,614 --> 00:05:27,868
It's about 60 yards.

115
00:05:28,601 --> 00:05:32,758
So 60 yard with almost
1.5 people per yard.

116
00:05:32,759 --> 00:05:33,895
That's 90.

117
00:05:33,896 --> 00:05:35,883
That's almost 100 people
just across.

118
00:05:35,898 --> 00:05:37,181
The way the ground
is trampled,

119
00:05:37,182 --> 00:05:39,110
you got to figure five
or tens times that amount

120
00:05:39,111 --> 00:05:40,228
of people came through here.

121
00:05:40,229 --> 00:05:43,355
Almost a thousand people?
Where are they going?

122
00:05:44,203 --> 00:05:46,036
South Texas, Mexico.

123
00:05:46,300 --> 00:05:47,535
Anyplace warmer.

124
00:05:47,805 --> 00:05:49,715
It'd take weeks
to get there by foot.

125
00:05:49,724 --> 00:05:51,913
God know how many thousand
people have the same idea.

126
00:05:51,914 --> 00:05:53,554
Mexico's borders
could be closed.

127
00:05:53,555 --> 00:05:55,734
We don't even know if
there still is a Mexico.

128
00:05:56,932 --> 00:05:58,341
Maybe we should try
to catch on with them.

129
00:05:58,342 --> 00:06:02,219
We can barely feed ourselves,
let alone... hundreds more.

130
00:06:04,609 --> 00:06:05,728
We got to keep going.

131
00:06:08,236 --> 00:06:09,394
Let's go.

132
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:20,302
Excuse me.
I'll be right back.

133
00:06:24,084 --> 00:06:25,290
Hey. Glad you came down.

134
00:06:26,032 --> 00:06:26,901
Thank you.

135
00:06:27,516 --> 00:06:29,310
- What time did you, uh...
- Early...

136
00:06:29,445 --> 00:06:30,738
late, I guess.

137
00:06:30,804 --> 00:06:32,859
I didn't want to wake you,
you looked so peaceful.

138
00:06:32,860 --> 00:06:34,519
Peaceful? Really?

139
00:06:34,616 --> 00:06:37,307
Did you have another one of those
bad dreams? Keep on there.

140
00:06:37,488 --> 00:06:39,543
I guess neither one of
us got much sleep.

141
00:06:40,359 --> 00:06:43,185
All I could do was think about
all these people down here, you know.

142
00:06:43,311 --> 00:06:45,896
And then I remembered about the
clothes we had in the attic.

143
00:06:45,897 --> 00:06:47,550
I thought that sweater
looked familiar.

144
00:06:47,640 --> 00:06:49,531
Yeah, that woman was on
layover in Kansas City

145
00:06:49,532 --> 00:06:50,534
when the bombs went off,

146
00:06:50,881 --> 00:06:53,220
Her husband and two kids
were waiting for her at home.

147
00:06:53,254 --> 00:06:54,064
Where?

148
00:06:54,103 --> 00:06:55,029
Denver.

149
00:06:56,881 --> 00:06:58,367
I lead these people here.

150
00:06:58,485 --> 00:07:00,414
For better or worse
this is their home now.

151
00:07:00,491 --> 00:07:02,555
It's on me to make sure
they're taken care of.

152
00:07:03,366 --> 00:07:05,006
Yeah, of course.

153
00:07:05,893 --> 00:07:07,263
What can I do to help, huh?

154
00:07:08,589 --> 00:07:10,981
Talk to them,
follow your instincts.

155
00:07:12,042 --> 00:07:13,219
The truth is...

156
00:07:13,315 --> 00:07:15,110
I'm winging this myself.

157
00:07:23,053 --> 00:07:24,191
I'll be outside.
Here.

158
00:07:30,210 --> 00:07:31,927
Should be back
before dark.

159
00:07:33,259 --> 00:07:34,474
And if you're not?

160
00:07:37,643 --> 00:07:39,688
Just tell me when I
should start to worry.

161
00:07:40,016 --> 00:07:41,386
This is the last time,

162
00:07:41,637 --> 00:07:42,466
okay?

163
00:07:43,430 --> 00:07:44,762
After today

164
00:07:45,205 --> 00:07:46,382
I'm here...

165
00:07:48,408 --> 00:07:49,700
for good, huh?

166
00:07:51,233 --> 00:07:52,082
Okay.

167
00:07:52,699 --> 00:07:54,262
I'll hold you to that.

168
00:08:05,543 --> 00:08:06,353
Hi, honey.

169
00:08:06,970 --> 00:08:08,195
How'd it go this morning?

170
00:08:08,417 --> 00:08:09,691
The whole thing
was a bust.

171
00:08:09,729 --> 00:08:10,983
I'm sorry, hon.

172
00:08:11,108 --> 00:08:12,073
Jake's out there now.

173
00:08:12,074 --> 00:08:13,231
Hopefully he and Stanley

174
00:08:13,232 --> 00:08:14,736
will have better luck
than I did.

175
00:08:15,015 --> 00:08:15,816
Is April here?

176
00:08:15,817 --> 00:08:16,867
No, she's at
the clinic.

177
00:08:16,868 --> 00:08:18,815
She promised me
she'd take a nap.

178
00:08:19,018 --> 00:08:21,526
I hope it is warmer in that
clinic than it is in this house.

179
00:08:21,527 --> 00:08:23,532
I think this house has
dropped ten degrees

180
00:08:23,533 --> 00:08:24,612
in the last hour.

181
00:08:25,442 --> 00:08:27,159
Feels like a storm's
coming in.

182
00:08:28,384 --> 00:08:31,316
We'd better seal up these
windows the best was we can.

183
00:08:31,452 --> 00:08:33,574
Been going around collecting
old sheets and linens.

184
00:08:33,575 --> 00:08:35,851
We'll shove them
underneath the doors.

185
00:08:36,160 --> 00:08:37,433
Look what I found...

186
00:08:37,780 --> 00:08:39,459
hidden in Jake's closet.

187
00:08:41,639 --> 00:08:43,539
Lord knows how long
that's been there.

188
00:08:43,635 --> 00:08:45,738
Well, at least he was
drinking the good stuff.

189
00:08:45,777 --> 00:08:48,555
I used to hide the most awful
rotgut in the world

190
00:08:48,556 --> 00:08:50,214
behind my mother's
china cabinet.

191
00:08:55,419 --> 00:08:56,441
What do you think?

192
00:08:57,927 --> 00:08:59,297
On an empty stomach?

193
00:09:00,030 --> 00:09:01,303
I'll get the glasses.

194
00:10:04,483 --> 00:10:06,326
Why would anyone destroy all this.

195
00:10:06,337 --> 00:10:09,421
If they'd wanted it out of commission,
they could have just taken it.

196
00:10:09,436 --> 00:10:11,396
Be worth a fortune after the E.M.P.

197
00:10:12,029 --> 00:10:13,659
Maybe there wasn't time,

198
00:10:13,723 --> 00:10:16,306
or maybe they didn't
care about this stuff.

199
00:10:23,686 --> 00:10:25,628
- How long?
- A couple of days...

200
00:10:25,719 --> 00:10:26,780
Give or take.

201
00:10:27,277 --> 00:10:29,286
But we just heard
from him yesterday.

202
00:10:31,048 --> 00:10:32,620
We heard from someone.

203
00:10:32,852 --> 00:10:34,054
Remote uplink.

204
00:10:34,424 --> 00:10:36,620
Somebody else using
his access codes.

205
00:10:36,643 --> 00:10:38,354
Who could have done this?

206
00:10:46,417 --> 00:10:48,088
Wager for the first kill.

207
00:10:48,654 --> 00:10:50,237
I'm in for a dozen eggs.

208
00:10:51,509 --> 00:10:53,075
Two hours chopping wood.

209
00:10:53,422 --> 00:10:55,064
Tax return consultation.

210
00:10:56,916 --> 00:10:59,199
Oh, how about
foot massages for a week?

211
00:10:59,592 --> 00:11:01,095
For me, not for him.

212
00:11:02,072 --> 00:11:03,090
We'll talk.

213
00:11:03,113 --> 00:11:04,344
Stanley, stop.

214
00:11:10,154 --> 00:11:12,836
- What are they doing?
- They're blocking the whole road.

215
00:11:12,894 --> 00:11:14,651
More like staking it out.

216
00:11:15,893 --> 00:11:17,373
All right, turn around.

217
00:11:17,379 --> 00:11:18,738
And... and go where?

218
00:11:18,739 --> 00:11:22,593
I don't know. Just do it, all right?
Turn around. We'll find another road.

219
00:11:42,012 --> 00:11:43,781
I see it. Damn it.

220
00:11:48,247 --> 00:11:50,108
Why are they following us?

221
00:11:55,970 --> 00:11:57,036
Stanley, gun it!

222
00:12:06,931 --> 00:12:08,319
This should get us
back to the highway.

223
00:12:08,320 --> 00:12:09,187
Then what?

224
00:12:09,188 --> 00:12:11,445
We try to make it back home,
find the patrol.

225
00:12:11,773 --> 00:12:13,653
Maybe they'll give up by then
or run out of gas.

226
00:12:13,664 --> 00:12:15,335
Yeah, if we don't first.

227
00:12:15,775 --> 00:12:17,640
Stanley...
Stanley, hold on!

228
00:12:19,467 --> 00:12:21,451
Doesn't look like
he put up much of a fight.

229
00:12:21,452 --> 00:12:23,203
He was probably out
before he knew what hit him.

230
00:12:23,204 --> 00:12:25,454
He must have trusted whoever did it.

231
00:12:25,789 --> 00:12:29,049
The thing is, whoever it was,

232
00:12:29,858 --> 00:12:32,020
they knew what
they were doing there,

233
00:12:32,289 --> 00:12:33,561
not over here.

234
00:12:33,700 --> 00:12:36,058
I mean, look at this.
It's a mess.

235
00:12:36,059 --> 00:12:38,829
But the drives...
They look like they're still intact.

236
00:12:38,830 --> 00:12:42,070
The old man had information
on the entire team...

237
00:12:42,071 --> 00:12:44,079
Contact information,
backgrounds...

238
00:12:44,080 --> 00:12:45,595
Last known whereabouts.

239
00:12:47,066 --> 00:12:49,147
Let's find out where everybody is.

240
00:12:51,743 --> 00:12:53,058
We can't outrun them.

241
00:12:53,059 --> 00:12:55,045
- How far till Jericho?
- Too far.

242
00:12:57,060 --> 00:12:58,071
Oh, God!

243
00:13:07,117 --> 00:13:08,134
Stay down.

244
00:13:15,388 --> 00:13:16,532
Stay down.

245
00:13:35,523 --> 00:13:37,345
Give me that drive you got there.

246
00:13:38,164 --> 00:13:40,021
Must feel good to be back
in the saddle, huh?

247
00:13:40,569 --> 00:13:43,169
I wish we didn't have
to come out here in the first place.

248
00:13:43,170 --> 00:13:46,099
What, are you getting soft on me?
Too much domestic bliss?

249
00:13:46,100 --> 00:13:47,696
Not quite bliss.

250
00:13:49,034 --> 00:13:51,570
There.
There it is. We're in.

251
00:14:16,271 --> 00:14:17,302
Thank you.

252
00:14:18,718 --> 00:14:20,509
Karaoke bullfighter, right?

253
00:14:20,510 --> 00:14:21,566
Excuse me?

254
00:14:21,567 --> 00:14:23,081
At that bar in Barcelona.

255
00:14:23,104 --> 00:14:26,613
