277
00:15:48,389 --> 00:15:49,678
You going hunting

278
00:15:50,869 --> 00:15:52,314
all those weekends...

279
00:15:54,605 --> 00:15:57,761
Why that kid got sit
in a deer stand for hours?

280
00:15:59,380 --> 00:16:02,027
We wouldn't say a word
to each other. Just...

281
00:16:03,033 --> 00:16:04,721
be in the woods together.

282
00:16:07,626 --> 00:16:11,488
I was always afraid that Jake
would forget about that.

283
00:16:11,511 --> 00:16:14,829
You know, that he'd grow up only
remembering the bad times. That we were

284
00:16:16,872 --> 00:16:19,998
That he wouldn't remember
that we had been close.

285
00:16:19,999 --> 00:16:24,397
That we were... buddies once.

286
00:16:29,075 --> 00:16:30,312
He remembers...

287
00:16:34,705 --> 00:16:35,965
deep down.

288
00:16:38,458 --> 00:16:41,175
That's why you mean
so much to him.

289
00:16:44,204 --> 00:16:46,042
Boy, that wind sounds awful.

290
00:16:47,811 --> 00:16:50,366
I hope Stanley and Jake
are okay out there.

291
00:17:45,119 --> 00:17:46,180
What happened?

292
00:17:46,761 --> 00:17:48,455
Jake, Stanley's not moving.

293
00:17:48,484 --> 00:17:50,461
- What?
- Stanley's not moving.

294
00:17:58,789 --> 00:18:00,198
Oh, my God. Go hide.

295
00:18:01,899 --> 00:18:03,083
- Go hide.
- No

296
00:18:03,368 --> 00:18:04,579
- Go on.
- No, No. Stanley...

297
00:18:04,580 --> 00:18:06,455
You'll be fine.
Go! Go hide!

298
00:19:27,094 --> 00:19:29,041
Come on.
Help me with Stanley.

299
00:19:30,850 --> 00:19:31,955
I can't move.

300
00:19:36,090 --> 00:19:37,697
Ritts, Woodworth, Pierce.

301
00:19:38,634 --> 00:19:39,674
That's half the team.

302
00:19:40,113 --> 00:19:42,391
We're being hunted.
It's worse than that.

303
00:19:43,385 --> 00:19:44,975
It's Woodworth and his wife.

304
00:19:45,333 --> 00:19:47,498
They were in Richmond.
That's his daughter.

305
00:19:47,923 --> 00:19:50,084
Anyone close to us
is in danger, too.

306
00:19:50,419 --> 00:19:51,622
No loose ends.

307
00:19:52,366 --> 00:19:53,600
Don't worry about your family.

308
00:19:53,620 --> 00:19:55,718
We're not going to let
anything happen to them.

309
00:19:55,719 --> 00:19:57,542
It's just us, Chavez
and Cheung left.

310
00:19:57,633 --> 00:19:59,858
We'll get back out on the field,
stay in the weeds

311
00:19:59,859 --> 00:20:01,555
until we can connect
with the chief.

312
00:20:01,903 --> 00:20:02,984
Here. Look at this.

313
00:20:07,850 --> 00:20:08,892
What is that?

314
00:20:09,239 --> 00:20:11,111
If we are being hunted,

315
