327
00:21:05,292 --> 00:21:06,623
It's gone.

328
00:21:06,642 --> 00:21:08,620
All right, get the jack.
The jack's back there.

329
00:21:09,306 --> 00:21:10,888
They took everything.

330
00:21:19,493 --> 00:21:20,804
How was your bath?

331
00:21:23,428 --> 00:21:25,859
Lukewarm, then luke-cold,

332
00:21:26,118 --> 00:21:27,275
then pretty much icy.

333
00:21:28,220 --> 00:21:30,439
- Look. Remember this?
- Oh, yeah.

334
00:21:30,440 --> 00:21:32,909
Times Square,
New Year's Eve, 2005.

335
00:21:33,372 --> 00:21:34,317
Wasted.

336
00:21:34,664 --> 00:21:36,266
That hangover was epic.

337
00:21:40,122 --> 00:21:43,460
Do you remember the last thing I said to
you the night before you left Jericho ?

338
00:21:43,547 --> 00:21:45,708
That I was selfish
and I didn't listen?

339
00:21:45,709 --> 00:21:46,730
Something like that?

340
00:21:47,733 --> 00:21:50,588
You have no idea how that ate
at me while you were gone.

341
00:21:50,839 --> 00:21:53,830
- I just kept thinking that was
the last  - You were right.

342
00:21:57,252 --> 00:22:02,674
You know, today,
seeing you with those people...

343
00:22:03,966 --> 00:22:05,703
It was like you had found yourself.

344
00:22:07,574 --> 00:22:09,927
I'm still just trying to figure
it out, you know?

345
00:22:12,068 --> 00:22:13,592
We're not these people anymore.

346
00:22:20,165 --> 00:22:22,354
But I'll tell you the one thing
that hasn't changed.

347
00:22:22,577 --> 00:22:24,043
The one constant.

348
00:22:24,602 --> 00:22:25,567
I love you.

349
00:22:26,533 --> 00:22:28,154
And it's going
to take a whole lot more

350
00:22:28,155 --> 00:22:30,199
than the end of the world
to change that.

351
00:22:41,586 --> 00:22:43,998
- How are your legs?
- I don't know I can't feel anything.

352
00:22:44,866 --> 00:22:45,946
The ground's
frozen solid.

353
00:22:45,947 --> 00:22:47,218
It's sucking the heat
right out of you.

354
00:22:47,219 --> 00:22:48,512
Why can't we build a fire?

355
00:22:48,589 --> 00:22:49,939
You smell the fumes?

356
00:22:50,113 --> 00:22:51,869
You have to get back to town.

357
00:22:52,004 --> 00:22:53,450
All right. I'm going
to try and go.

358
00:22:54,457 --> 00:22:56,155
No. You can't on that ankle.

359
00:22:56,527 --> 00:22:58,509
- I'll go.
- No. Those guys are still out there.

360
00:22:58,510 --> 00:22:59,763
They went the other way.

361
00:22:59,859 --> 00:23:02,541
Jericho has a patrol
five miles out of town.

362
00:23:02,637 --> 00:23:04,123
We can't have come
more than ten.

363
00:23:04,219 --> 00:23:05,686
Jake, it's too dangerous.

364
00:23:05,736 --> 00:23:06,778
What are our options?

365
00:23:06,797 --> 00:23:08,167
With no bags, no fire?

366
00:23:08,244 --> 00:23:10,637
All right, one of you goes
or we all die here.

367
00:23:14,997 --> 00:23:16,694
All right, fine, fine.

368
00:23:17,879 --> 00:23:20,988
I threw a flashlight over there
somewhere. You might need it.

369
00:23:23,571 --> 00:23:24,574
Listen...

370
00:23:25,808 --> 00:23:28,066
stay on the shoulder
the whole time, okay?

371
00:23:28,386 --> 00:23:30,894
If you see any headlights
or you hear any engines,

372
00:23:32,167 --> 00:23:33,576
get low and hide,

373
00:23:33,672 --> 00:23:35,466
all right?
Now, you're gonna
want to head

374
00:23:35,983 --> 00:23:36,976
southeast.

375
00:23:38,114 --> 00:23:40,468
Stanley, that doesn't mean
anything to me.

376
00:23:43,323 --> 00:23:44,674
Stay on this road.

377
00:23:44,789 --> 00:23:46,410
Stay on this road
and then you make...

378
00:23:46,467 --> 00:23:47,934
make your first left

379
00:23:48,184 --> 00:23:49,998
Okay?
And you're gonna go about a mile

380
00:23:50,095 --> 00:23:51,957
and then you're gonna make
your second right,

381
00:23:52,410 --> 00:23:55,342
and you're gonna make another right
and then another left.

382
00:23:55,419 --> 00:23:58,476
And then once you get to the crossroads
of the highway, you're home free...

383
00:23:58,969 --> 00:24:01,573
You'll see a big sign pointing
to the way to Jericho, okay?

384
00:24:01,612 --> 00:24:02,827
Got it?

385
00:24:03,281 --> 00:24:05,181
Left, second right.

386
00:24:05,615 --> 00:24:06,946
Right, left,

387
00:24:06,985 --> 00:24:07,785
Right.

388
00:24:12,514 --> 00:24:13,922
Mimi, I...

389
00:24:14,153 --> 00:24:15,215
Don't worry.

390
00:24:15,909 --> 00:24:16,874
Don't worry.

391
00:24:17,124 --> 00:24:18,243
I'll be careful.

392
00:24:32,836 --> 00:24:34,225
<i>Here's what we're gonna do:</i>

393
00:24:34,226 --> 00:24:36,038
I know a place that's safe.

394
00:24:36,347 --> 00:24:38,662
We take Darcy and the kids
out of Jericho

395
00:24:38,758 --> 00:24:41,362
and stash them before you and I
get back on the move.

396
00:24:41,681 --> 00:24:43,340
I am not leaving them alone.

397
00:24:43,341 --> 00:24:45,076
- I don't think you have a choice.
- No...

398
00:24:45,077 --> 00:24:47,314
See, because I've got leverage.

399
00:24:47,777 --> 00:24:50,709
If they kill me, they will
never find the package.

400
00:24:51,094 --> 00:24:52,850
It's not you
they're gonna kill.

401
00:24:53,255 --> 00:24:55,975
It'll be Sam
or Darcy or me;

402
00:24:57,152 --> 00:24:59,660
anything they can use
to get to you.

403
00:25:04,234 --> 00:25:06,626
Anything they can
use to get to me.

404
00:25:10,917 --> 00:25:12,094
The body.

405
00:25:12,933 --> 00:25:15,402
These... These, uh...

406
00:25:16,488 --> 00:25:20,057
...these half-smashed drives,

407
00:25:20,983 --> 00:25:22,951
<i>...this whole...</i>

408
00:25:23,337 --> 00:25:24,687
this whole setup--

409
00:25:25,208 --> 00:25:26,944
If someone had wanted
to destroy all this,

410
00:25:26,945 --> 00:25:28,555
why leave the house
standing, huh?

411
00:25:28,767 --> 00:25:30,793
Why not just burn it all down?

412
00:25:31,458 --> 00:25:33,311
Someone wanted us
to see all this.

413
00:25:42,207 --> 00:25:43,480
We're being played.

414
00:25:44,117 --> 00:25:45,959
Why would anyone go through
all that trouble?

415
00:25:46,209 --> 00:25:47,232
I don't know,

416
00:25:47,695 --> 00:25:48,968
but this is all too big now.

417
00:25:48,969 --> 00:25:50,424
There's too many angles
to cover.

418
00:25:50,425 --> 00:25:51,659
Too many unknowns.

419
00:25:53,434 --> 00:25:54,533
I need to get home.

420
00:25:54,534 --> 00:25:55,826
- Robert, wait.
- What?

421
00:25:58,180 --> 00:25:59,337
Let's think about this.

422
00:25:59,338 --> 00:26:01,170
What's the plan?
What are you going to do?

423
00:26:01,415 --> 00:26:04,926
You know, maybe the plan all
along was to get us out here.

424
00:26:05,852 --> 00:26:07,453
I gotta protect
my family, Sarah.

425
00:26:08,495 --> 00:26:09,826
And what about the package?

426
00:26:13,087 --> 00:26:14,620
It'll need to be moved.

427
00:26:30,132 --> 00:26:31,792
This isn't so bad, right?

428
00:26:31,841 --> 00:26:33,364
Hey, we've been
through worse.

429
00:26:33,407 --> 00:26:35,138
Remember the time we got stuck on
the roof of the...

430
00:26:35,139 --> 00:26:37,205
town hall in the middle
of a lightning storm, huh?

431
00:26:37,572 --> 00:26:39,501
We were so afraid the lightning
was going to...

432
00:26:39,867 --> 00:26:41,256
blow up the fireworks.

433
00:26:41,911 --> 00:26:45,094
You squealed like a little girl
wanting to jump off that roof.

434
00:26:45,095 --> 00:26:45,982
That was you.

435
00:26:46,329 --> 00:26:47,872
Your voice hadn't changed yet.

436
00:26:48,528 --> 00:26:51,133
Please, I had you beat by,
like, six months.

437
00:26:53,884 --> 00:26:55,138
Drink some water.

438
00:26:56,373 --> 00:26:57,415
It's frozen right through.

439
00:26:57,839 --> 00:26:58,785
What?

440
00:27:04,775 --> 00:27:07,842
I saw an abandoned cabin about
a quarter mile up the road.

441
00:27:07,881 --> 00:27:09,058
You need to get inside.

442
00:27:10,524 --> 00:27:12,222
It'll hurt, but you can make it.

443
00:27:12,241 --> 00:27:13,958
- Jake, I'm staying.
- Listen to me!

444
00:27:14,657 --> 00:27:17,976
There's no point in both of us
freezing to death out there.

445
00:27:18,554 --> 00:27:20,580
- She's coming back.
- When?

446
00:27:21,912 --> 00:27:23,359
She's been gone for, like,
an hour.

447
00:27:23,360 --> 00:27:25,317
It'll take her a little while to
reach the patrol,

448
00:27:25,318 --> 00:27:26,976
but when she does,
she'll find someone.

449
00:27:26,977 --> 00:27:28,153
I know she'll find someone.

450
00:27:28,925 --> 00:27:30,642
Unless somebody finds her first.

451
00:27:31,201 --> 00:27:32,146
Look,

452
00:27:32,182 --> 00:27:34,536
it's gonna get dark soon,
you need to go.

453
00:27:43,067 --> 00:27:45,498
You wouldn't leave me
any more than I'm leaving you.

454
00:27:48,836 --> 00:27:50,842
Mimi's strong.
She'll find her way.

455
00:28:03,441 --> 00:28:04,599
Wait...

456
00:28:04,600 --> 00:28:06,354
he said keep going east.

457
00:28:07,782 --> 00:28:09,383
No... southeast.

458
00:28:11,066 --> 00:28:14,461
And... look for a sign.

459
00:28:27,525 --> 00:28:29,454
Oh, God, I hate this place!

460
00:29:04,493 --> 00:29:05,612
Come on, man.

461
00:29:06,215 --> 00:29:07,276
You can't fall asleep.

462
00:29:07,372 --> 00:29:08,703
You got to stay up;
come on.

463
00:29:08,736 --> 00:29:10,029
You stopped shivering.
Come on.

464
00:29:10,030 --> 00:29:12,011
You got to talk to me--
come on, come on, buddy.

465
00:29:12,012 --> 00:29:13,314
You gotta talk to me.

466
00:29:13,353 --> 00:29:14,780
Talk to me, buddy.
Come on.

467
00:29:15,128 --> 00:29:16,325
I'm sorry.

468
00:29:16,420 --> 00:29:17,540
I'm really sorry.

469
00:29:17,541 --> 00:29:18,795
About what?

470
00:29:19,526 --> 00:29:21,031
Five years ago.

471
00:29:21,223 --> 00:29:23,056
Sorry I left the way I did.

472
00:29:23,635 --> 00:29:25,178
Iit's okay. It doesn't matter.

473
00:29:25,429 --> 00:29:26,394
Doesn't matter.

474
00:29:26,395 --> 00:29:27,771
I was gonna call.

475
00:29:30,183 --> 00:29:31,243
I was gonna call.

476
00:29:31,244 --> 00:29:33,954
I know. Listen, I want you
to forget about it, okay?

477
00:29:33,955 --> 00:29:36,276
We never got to go backpacking
