482
00:29:42,352 --> 00:29:44,029
We're gonna sleep
on the beach.

483
00:29:44,260 --> 00:29:46,188
As soon as the planes
are up and running again,

484
00:29:46,189 --> 00:29:47,435
it's gonna be you and me.

485
00:29:47,570 --> 00:29:49,923
Hell, you can fly us
there yourself, huh?

486
00:29:49,924 --> 00:29:52,556
Come on. Come on.
Tell me something good, man.

487
00:29:52,557 --> 00:29:55,620
I haven't talked to you in five years.
You've been gone for five years.

488
00:29:56,753 --> 00:29:58,895
Tell me... Hey, tell me
about San Diego.

489
00:29:58,896 --> 00:30:00,000
How was it?

490
00:30:00,964 --> 00:30:02,758
- Warm.
- Warm, right.

491
00:30:03,395 --> 00:30:05,209
Beaches, blondes, huh?

492
00:30:06,377 --> 00:30:07,978
What were you doing there?

493
00:30:08,056 --> 00:30:10,158
Flying, flying planes.

494
00:30:10,236 --> 00:30:12,917
Really?
That's cool, man.

495
00:30:12,994 --> 00:30:15,483
Your grandfather
would've been psyched, huh?

496
00:30:15,592 --> 00:30:18,080
Did you have a girl there?
I know you had a girl.

497
00:30:18,428 --> 00:30:19,836
She's dead.

498
00:30:25,570 --> 00:30:26,805
What do you mean?

499
00:30:27,596 --> 00:30:29,081
You don't know that.

500
00:30:29,082 --> 00:30:31,965
I mean, it all depends on where she was
when the bombs went off, right?

501
00:30:31,966 --> 00:30:33,551
I mean, she could
have made it, right?

502
00:30:33,570 --> 00:30:35,451
- Tell me what her name was.
- She's dead....

503
00:30:35,452 --> 00:30:36,705
It was my fault.

504
00:30:36,706 --> 00:30:38,372
- It's not your fault.
- Let me lay down.

505
00:30:38,373 --> 00:30:39,627
- Jake, no.
- Let me lay down.

506
00:30:39,628 --> 00:30:41,499
It wasn't your fault.
Come on... Come on...

507
00:30:41,749 --> 00:30:43,650
Come on, stay with me.
You gotta stay with me.

508
00:30:45,154 --> 00:30:47,161
Come on, Jake.

509
00:30:47,453 --> 00:30:49,402
Stay with me, Jake.
Come on, man.

510
00:30:52,392 --> 00:30:53,607
Stay with me.

