00:31:23,384 --> 00:31:24,850
Gotta keep moving.

514
00:31:50,063 --> 00:31:52,783
Please don't hurt me...
please don't hurt me.

515
00:31:52,822 --> 00:31:54,346
Please don't hurt me!

516
00:31:54,654 --> 00:31:56,063
Please don't hurt me...

517
00:31:56,410 --> 00:31:57,437
Mimi?

518
00:32:00,673 --> 00:32:03,605
- It's Gail and Johnston Green, honey.
You're safe.  - Oh, thanks God!

519
00:32:03,808 --> 00:32:05,516
Come on, baby,
let's get out of here.

520
00:32:05,844 --> 00:32:06,886
Come on.

521
00:32:15,065 --> 00:32:16,416
Those are hideous.

522
00:32:16,417 --> 00:32:18,422
Are those the sheets
from your old apartment?

523
00:32:18,769 --> 00:32:21,085
Because you can't expect
anyone to sleep on those.

524
00:32:21,543 --> 00:32:24,514
If anyone asks, we'll pretend
someone else donated them.

525
00:32:33,755 --> 00:32:34,777
Your dress.

526
00:32:37,362 --> 00:32:38,983
Guess I shouldn't be seeing this, huh?

527
00:32:40,449 --> 00:32:42,571
The day's sort of come and gone, so...

528
00:32:44,499 --> 00:32:45,599
It'll come again.

529
00:32:46,313 --> 00:32:47,316
You think?

530
00:32:49,092 --> 00:32:50,211
I do.

531
00:32:51,677 --> 00:32:53,703
I tell you what, I've got
a pack of Ramen noodles

532
00:32:53,704 --> 00:32:55,304
with your name on it,
what do you say?

533
00:32:55,728 --> 00:32:58,622
Great. I'll deliver this to the shelter
and come back and wash up.

534
00:32:59,181 --> 00:33:00,590
Roger, wait.

535
00:33:02,267 --> 00:33:03,637
I'll come with you.

536
00:33:20,210 --> 00:33:21,869
It's Mom and Dad, honey!

537
00:33:22,505 --> 00:33:24,357
Stanley, you all right, sweetheart?

538
00:33:25,282 --> 00:33:27,385
You need to go get in the truck
and get warm, pal.

539
00:33:27,386 --> 00:33:29,064
- Where's Mimi?
- I'm right here.

540
00:33:29,123 --> 00:33:30,435
Stanley, I'm right here.

541
00:33:33,116 --> 00:33:35,026
Wake up. Wake up!

542
00:33:35,875 --> 00:33:37,071
Wake up, Jake.

543
00:33:37,476 --> 00:33:38,479
Wake up.

544
00:33:38,784 --> 00:33:39,884
Wake up. Oh, thank God.

545
00:33:39,885 --> 00:33:41,234
We're gonna help you, honey.

546
00:33:43,453 --> 00:33:44,784
We saw the storm coming

547
00:33:45,093 --> 00:33:47,254
and we started to worry
when you hadn't come back.

548
00:33:47,255 --> 00:33:48,353
Sweetheart...

549
00:33:51,093 --> 00:33:51,942
Honey,

550
00:33:51,943 --> 00:33:54,160
we're not gonna be able
to get this truck off of him.

551
00:33:54,161 --> 00:33:56,050
I need you to take
these guys back to town

552
00:33:56,051 --> 00:33:57,559
and get me some help out here.

553
00:33:57,560 --> 00:34:00,217
You signal when you're coming back
so I know it's you, all right?

554
00:34:00,218 --> 00:34:02,628
- I'll flash the lights.
- All right, go, go, go!

555
00:34:04,806 --> 00:34:06,234
Jake, look at me, son.

556
00:34:06,235 --> 00:34:07,237
Lookie here.

557
00:34:07,545 --> 00:34:09,764
You're gonna make it, son...
I know you.

558
00:34:10,748 --> 00:34:13,449
I know what you're made of.
You're gonna be all right.

559
00:34:13,989 --> 00:34:16,593
You're gonna make it.
Stay with me now.

560
00:34:30,114 --> 00:34:32,738
Robert, please,
the kids are sleeping.

561
00:34:33,297 --> 00:34:35,863
- I'm sorry.
- What on earth are you doing?

562
00:34:36,206 --> 00:34:37,730
Oh, I'm sorry.

563
00:34:50,484 --> 00:34:52,355
Jake, you'll be home real soon,

564
00:34:52,761 --> 00:34:54,844
but you got to stay
with me now. Come on.

565
00:34:57,207 --> 00:34:59,050
Leave me here.
Leave me alone.

566
00:34:59,320 --> 00:35:00,979
Now, I'm not going anywhere.

567
00:35:01,539 --> 00:35:03,101
But you got to hang on.

568
00:35:03,410 --> 00:35:05,301
Now, they'll be here soon, son.

569
00:35:07,346 --> 00:35:08,358
Dad...

570
00:35:08,975 --> 00:35:10,220
I'm sorry.

571
00:35:11,065 --> 00:35:13,187
Oh, son, you got nothing
to be sorry about.

572
00:35:18,011 --> 00:35:19,959
Open your eyes, Jake.
Come on, now.

573
00:35:20,808 --> 00:35:22,950
Look at me.
Look at me, Jake.

574
00:35:25,226 --> 00:35:26,712
I can see her.

575
00:35:28,757 --> 00:35:29,895
See who?

576
00:35:31,496 --> 00:35:32,866
The girl.

577
00:35:35,161 --> 00:35:36,801
What... girl?

578
00:35:36,802 --> 00:35:38,538
Jake, I think you're hallucinating, son.

579
00:35:38,539 --> 00:35:39,561
No, listen to me.

580
00:35:41,934 --> 00:35:43,670
When I was in Iraq...

581
00:35:46,082 --> 00:35:47,683
... there was a girl.

582
00:35:50,018 --> 00:35:51,735
She couldn't have been more than...

583
00:35:52,426 --> 00:35:53,583
10 or 12...

584
00:35:54,490 --> 00:35:55,841
Don't talk now, son.

585
00:35:56,033 --> 00:35:57,056
You save your energy.

586
00:35:57,057 --> 00:35:58,677
We'll talk when we get... home.

587
00:35:59,989 --> 00:36:01,493
I killed her, Dad.

588
00:36:07,378 --> 00:36:09,075
I killed a little girl.

589
00:36:31,717 --> 00:36:33,048
Hurry up!

590
00:36:46,089 --> 00:36:47,575
Open your eyes, Jake.

591
00:36:47,576 --> 00:36:48,945
Open your eyes.

592
00:36:50,237 --> 00:36:52,011
All right, everyone on three...

593
00:36:52,012 --> 00:36:53,015
One,

594
00:36:53,343 --> 00:36:54,828
two, three!

595
00:37:00,171 --> 00:37:01,271
All right, he's free.

596
00:37:01,773 --> 00:37:03,065
Let's get the board in here.

597
00:37:04,069 --> 00:37:05,902
One, two, three.

598
00:37:16,821 --> 00:37:17,844
You were right.

599
00:37:17,845 --> 00:37:20,776
I need to get my family
as far away from me as possible.

600
00:37:21,683 --> 00:37:23,187
I've been thinking, and...

601
00:37:23,978 --> 00:37:25,638
There's no other choice.

602
00:37:27,161 --> 00:37:28,898
You're doing the right thing.

603
00:37:30,345 --> 00:37:31,425
Listen.

604
00:37:33,355 --> 00:37:34,744
After they're safe,

605
00:37:35,265 --> 00:37:37,117
you and me need
to get back in the field.

606
00:37:37,618 --> 00:37:39,547
That's half our team gone, Sarah,

607
00:37:39,548 --> 00:37:41,762
and whoever did that
did it for a reason.

608
00:37:44,752 --> 00:37:46,431
How are you gonna tell Darcy?

609
00:37:49,497 --> 00:37:51,292
I'll tell her after I've moved them.

610
00:37:52,526 --> 00:37:55,189
She'll never agree if she knows
I won't be staying with them.

611
00:38:05,916 --> 00:38:07,845
He's better off here
than the med center.

612
00:38:08,096 --> 00:38:11,221
We're still on emergency power,
and it's... it's warmer here.

613
00:38:12,784 --> 00:38:14,115
Here, honey.

614
00:38:14,752 --> 00:38:16,002
What about his injuries?

615
00:38:16,003 --> 00:38:17,916
Well, the cut on his head
isn't very deep,

616
00:38:17,917 --> 00:38:20,053
and neither one
of his legs are broken.

617
00:38:20,786 --> 00:38:22,001
He's very lucky.

618
00:38:22,002 --> 00:38:23,313
I'm freezing.

619
00:38:23,738 --> 00:38:25,551
I'm gonna go get you
some more blankets.

620
00:38:26,033 --> 00:38:27,557
You're still hypothermic.

621
00:38:27,558 --> 00:38:30,567
It's just gonna take a few hours
for your body to stabilize.

622
00:38:32,264 --> 00:38:34,406
- Can we have a minute?
- Oh, sure.

623
00:38:49,840 --> 00:38:51,133
Dad...

624
00:38:55,782 --> 00:38:57,326
What I told you out there...

625
00:39:00,220 --> 00:39:01,802
please forget it.

626
00:39:03,500 --> 00:39:04,657
Please.

627
00:39:08,419 --> 00:39:09,847
Afraid I can't do that.

628
00:39:22,210 --> 00:39:24,564
I've seen a lot of things
in my time, Jake.

629
00:39:26,918 --> 00:39:28,133
I've been to war.

630
00:39:29,445 --> 00:39:32,821
I know what war can do.
I know what men can do... Terrible...

631
00:39:34,230 --> 00:39:35,716
... terrible things.

632
00:39:38,623 --> 00:39:39,974
I know what I did.

633
00:39:42,636 --> 00:39:44,141
You can talk to me.

634
00:40:09,607 --> 00:40:11,015
When you're ready, son.

635
00:40:14,354 --> 00:40:15,569
When you're ready.

636
00:40:33,608 --> 00:40:34,977
You okay?

637
00:40:43,273 --> 00:40:44,546
How's the sprain?

638
00:40:46,090 --> 00:40:49,119
I think it'd be better with painkillers,
but I'm not gonna complain.

639
00:40:50,025 --> 00:40:53,147
You know, for a while there, I didn't
think I'd ever feel anything again.

640
00:40:56,041 --> 00:40:57,545
When I was out there,

641
00:40:58,066 --> 00:40:59,398
just for a moment,

642
00:41:00,459 --> 00:41:02,234
I didn't think
I was gonna make it.

643
00:41:03,277 --> 00:41:05,940
And I stopped... to rest.

644
00:41:06,827 --> 00:41:09,316
And then I just didn't
even want to move.

645
00:41:12,904 --> 00:41:14,081
But you did.

646
00:41:15,586 --> 00:41:16,898
You did make it.

647
00:41:18,364 --> 00:41:19,927
And I knew you would.

648
00:41:26,582 --> 00:41:28,454
Your lips are still cold.

649
00:41:30,749 --> 00:41:32,601
Maybe you can warm them.

650
00:41:37,193 --> 00:41:39,450
That's the worst line
I've ever heard.

651
00:41:39,971 --> 00:41:41,881
I know. I've got others.

652
00:41:43,116 --> 00:41:44,717
- Shut up.
- Okay.

653
00:41:55,546 --> 00:41:56,879
Tomorrow morning...

654
00:41:59,040 --> 00:42:00,114
we're leaving.

655
00:42:01,423 --> 00:42:03,251
We're leaving?
For... for where?

656
00:42:05,201 --> 00:42:06,399
I don't know yet.

657
00:42:07,461 --> 00:42:08,633
You don't know?

658
00:42:13,141 --> 00:42:15,585
Darcy, when I came
to get you in DC...

659
00:42:17,697 --> 00:42:19,364
I told you it wasn't safe,

660
00:42:19,981 --> 00:42:21,587
but I couldn't tell you why.

661
00:42:27,119 --> 00:42:28,317
I'm going for a walk.

662
00:42:41,670 --> 00:42:43,477
I have something
in my possession.

663
00:42:45,691 --> 00:42:47,507
And there's people
out there that want it,

664
00:42:48,062 --> 00:42:50,235
that will stop at nothing to get it.

665
00:42:52,552 --> 00:42:54,152
And that puts you,
me and the kids

666
00:42:54,547 --> 00:42:55,673
in danger here.

667
00:43:01,827 --> 00:43:03,931
Okay, so th... then we go.

668
00:43:05,274 --> 00:43:06,479
<i>I trust you.</i>

669
00:43:12,188 --> 00:43:13,353
<i>Robert, do y...</i>

670
00:43:14,806 --> 00:43:15,873
Do you trust me?

671
00:43:18,866 --> 00:43:21,149
- You're late.
- You're impatient.

672
00:43:26,442 --> 00:43:27,933
Then listen to me.

673
00:43:28,812 --> 00:43:30,976
Okay, Sarah is not on our side.

674
00:43:31,440 --> 00:43:32,862
Now... whatever's...

675
00:43:33,365 --> 00:43:34,689
gone on between the two of you,

676
00:43:34,690 --> 00:43:37,010
I'm telling you, Robert,
she's not here to help us.

677
00:43:40,536 --> 00:43:42,018
Have you located the package?

678
00:43:42,729 --> 00:43:43,734
Soon.

679
00:43:45,177 --> 00:43:47,114
Hawkins is starting to put
the pieces together.

680
00:43:47,115 --> 00:43:49,643
- He needs to be eliminated.
- I know.

681
00:43:49,859 --> 00:43:52,764
We've already eliminated the other
three targets without incident.

682
00:43:52,765 --> 00:43:54,444
Why are you stalling on this one?

683
00:44:05,437 --> 00:44:07,205
Because this one is different.

684
00:44:08,503 --> 00:44:15,005
[ www.seriessub.com ]

